  1050→## Tips
  1052→### Sending form data
  1054→Sending form data in Ky is identical to `fetch`. Just pass a [`FormData`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData) instance to the `body` option. The `Content-Type` header will be automatically set to `multipart/form-data`, overriding any existing `Content-Type` header.
  1055→
  1056→```js
  1057→import ky from 'ky';
  1058→
  1059→// `multipart/form-data`
  1060→const formData = new FormData();
  1061→formData.append('food', 'fries');
  1062→formData.append('drink', 'icetea');
  1063→
  1064→const response = await ky.post(url, {body: formData});
  1065→```
  1066→
  1067→If you want to send the data in `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` format, you will need to encode the data with [`URLSearchParams`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/URLSearchParams). Like `FormData`, this will override any existing `Content-Type` headers.
  1068→
  1069→```js
  1070→import ky from 'ky';
  1071→
  1072→// `application/x-www-form-urlencoded`
  1073→const searchParams = new URLSearchParams();
  1074→searchParams.set('food', 'fries');
  1075→searchParams.set('drink', 'icetea');
  1076→
  1077→const response = await ky.post(url, {body: searchParams});
  1078→```
  1079→
