  1156→### Proxy support (Node.js) …
  1158→#### Native proxy support
  1160→Node.js 24.5+ supports automatic proxy configuration via environment variables. Set `NODE_USE_ENV_PROXY=1` or use the `--use-env-proxy` CLI flag.
  1161→
  1162→```sh
  1163→NODE_USE_ENV_PROXY=1 HTTP_PROXY=http://proxy.example.com:8080 node app.js
  1164→```
  1165→
  1166→Or:
  1167→
  1168→```sh
  1169→node --use-env-proxy app.js
  1170→```
  1171→
  1172→Supported environment variables:
  1173→- `HTTP_PROXY` / `http_proxy`: Proxy URL for HTTP requests
  1174→- `HTTPS_PROXY` / `https_proxy`: Proxy URL for HTTPS requests
  1175→- `NO_PROXY` / `no_proxy`: Comma-separated list of hosts to bypass the proxy
  1176→
